  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is a three-armed randomised controlled trial that aims to determine the effect of
      a structured educational programme on physical activity levels and glucose tolerance in
      individuals with impaired glucose tolerance (IGT). The educational programme is designed to
      promote physical activity by targeting perceptions and knowledge of IGT, exercise
      self-efficacy, and self-regulatory skills. The study will also investigate whether the
      effectiveness of the educational programme at promoting self-regulatory skills and physical
      activity is enhanced by the inclusion of a pedometer and personalised step/day goals.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
